definitions.definition: A biogeographical region of Southeastern Asia which encompasses the areas of the Asian continental shelf that was exposed during the last ice age
The area of the Sunda Shelf exposed during ice age glacial periods.

main_definition: ( biogeography ) A biogeographical region of Southeastern Asia which encompasses the areas of the Asian continental shelf that was exposed during the last ice age [from 1920s]
secondary_definitions: ( paleogeography ) The area of the Sunda Shelf exposed during ice age glacial periods.
